cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code, the trained model, or build on the methodology or findings, please cite this repository."
title: "MIME-mouse: a masked event-stream generative model of human mouse movement, near chance against kinematic detectors"
authors:
  - family-names: "Lau"
    given-names: "Aaron"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-07-07
url: "https://github.com/4LAU/MIME-mouse"
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - mouse dynamics
  - trajectory synthesis
  - generative models
  - masked transformer
  - human motor control
abstract: >-
  MIME (Mouse Imitation via Masked Events) is a 6M-parameter masked
  bidirectional Transformer over polar event streams that generates
  point-to-point mouse trajectories. After set-level adversarial reselection
  over cached candidate pools, a Random Forest detector reads near chance
  against held-out human movement (OOB AUC 0.504 at n=2000 on three tuning
  seeds, 0.513 on six fresh out-of-sample seeds). The repository includes the evaluation framework,
  the full experiment journal, trained weights, and cached pools that
  reproduce the headline number on CPU in minutes.
